body:
@dguy removed duplicated code.

I agree about checking for the new config first, but currently we set a default value on it.  So checking the new one first means we'll never get to an old config specified by the user. 

I think as long as we need to be backwards compatible, we can remove the default setting for the new configs.

@guozhangwang 
> I think we should not force setting the instance state to NOT_RUNNING at any point except in the close() call, even if the global thread dies. One reason is that in the close() call, we shutdown the metrics as metrics.close(); in the shutdown thread as well, if we just set it not running we are at the risk of leaking that metrics object without closing it.

I guess that means we need another state? If all threads are `DEAD` then the instance is not in the `RUNNING` state.
